Libra District \u8211\'96 Governmental Apex\line Expanded DetailSpecific Types of Locations1. The Grand Council Chambers\line The main legislative hall of Concordia. It features a large circular chamber with seating arranged by district representation. The architecture is grand and symmetrical, with excellent acoustics for debate. Major city-wide decisions, emergency declarations, and resource allocation votes take place here.2. Bureau of Resource Allocation\line The most high-pressure and heavily secured building in the district. This is where power, heat, siligel, and critical materials are distributed. The halls are filled with analysts, negotiators, and constantly updated holographic maps of the city\u8217\'92s needs. It is often loud, tense, and the site of frequent arguments.3. Treaty Archive Vaults\line Climate-controlled, secure archives containing historical treaties, the Falkland Treaty, pre-war agreements, and post-war accords. Researchers and diplomats frequently access these vaults when trying to interpret old laws in the context of the current crisis.4. Diplomatic Reception Halls\line Elegant, formal spaces used for negotiations between districts and factions. These halls are designed to project neutrality and professionalism, with soundproof meeting rooms and private negotiation chambers.5. Justice & Arbitration Courts\line Formal courtrooms where disputes between districts, factions, or individuals are heard and resolved. Cases range from resource theft accusations to ethical violations and inter-district conflicts.6. Public Policy Announcement Plazas\line Open plazas where major announcements are made to the public. During the energy crisis, these plazas often host tense gatherings where citizens voice frustration with central decisions.7. The Scales Atrium\line A grand central hall featuring a large symbolic sculpture representing balance and justice. It serves as a major meeting point, symbolic heart of the district, and venue for important ceremonies.8. Administrative Support Wings\line The behind-the-scenes offices where clerks, analysts, archivists, and support staff do the day-to-day bureaucratic work that keeps the Apex functioning.}
