Notable NPCs (Examples)Councilor Helena Voss\line A senior human administrator known for her calm demeanor and ability to broker difficult compromises. She is respected but increasingly exhausted by the impossible choices forced by the energy crisis. Many see her as one of the last true believers in balanced governance.Justice Unit-17\line A robot arbitrator known for his precise, logical approach and strict adherence to procedure. He has a reputation for being fair but emotionally distant. He struggles internally with the growing gap between legal ideals and survival realities.Theo\line A young human clerk working in the Bureau of Resource Allocation. He is idealistic but becoming increasingly disillusioned as he processes angry requests and makes decisions that always seem to hurt someone.Ambassador Lira Solen\line A human diplomat who specializes in negotiations with the Frostward Reaches and other frontier groups. She is pragmatic and skilled at finding creative solutions when standard procedures fail.Councilor Veyr-3\line A robot politician who represents more progressive and humanitarian viewpoints. He often clashes with more pragmatic members over whether to prioritize immediate survival or long-term ethical principles.}
