\par \pard\plain \s17\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
let's go into more detail with the Pisces district; specific types of locations, notable NPCs, daily life examples, etc)}
\par \pard\plain \s17\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Pisces District \u8211\'96 The Veil Market\line Expanded DetailSpecific Types of Locations1. The Shrouded Bazaar\line The main open-air (domed) market square. It is a chaotic, ever-changing maze of stalls, tents, pop-up shops, and mobile vendors. Goods range from scarce legal items at inflated prices to outright illegal or restricted technology. The lighting is low and atmospheric, with flickering neon and hanging lanterns.2. The Undergrid Exchange\line Hidden entrances and secure safehouses connected directly to the Undergrid tunnels. This is the primary route for smuggling operations. Many merchants and fixers have private access points here for moving goods in and out of the district.3. Shadow Auction Houses\line Private, invitation-only venues where rare pre-war artifacts, restricted technology, high-grade siligel, and other valuable items are auctioned. These locations are heavily guarded and operate on a strict \u8220\'93no questions asked\u8221\'94 basis.4. Fixer Bars & Safe Lounges\line Establishments where deals are negotiated, information is traded, and people can lie low. These places often have back rooms for private meetings and are run by people with strong reputations for discretion.5. Modification & Repair Dens\line Unofficial clinics and workshops offering gray-market or illegal augmentations, repairs, and custom technology. These dens range from relatively professional operations to risky back-alley setups.6. The Veil Archives\line A semi-secret repository of smuggled data, forbidden knowledge, black-market records, and recovered pre-war information. Access is usually granted through personal connections rather than official channels.7. Hidden Loading Docks\line Secure, disguised areas where contraband is loaded and unloaded. These docks are often connected to the Undergrid or use disguised surface transport. They operate mostly at night or during low-visibility periods.8. The Whisper Network Nodes\line Small, discreet locations (often disguised as regular stalls or lounges) that serve as hubs for the district\u8217\'92s informal information and favor-trading networks.}
\par \pard\plain \s21\rtlch\afs12 \ltrch\loch\sb0\sa283\brdrt\brdrnone\brdrl\brdrnone\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw1\brdrcf15\brsp0\brdrr\brdrnone\noline\fs12\ltrpar\loch

\par \pard\plain \s17\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Notable NPCs (Examples)Mira \u8220\'93Veil\u8221\'94 Kade\line A veteran human fixer with a strong reputation for reliability. She specializes in arranging difficult acquisitions (medicine, parts, restricted data) and has extensive contacts across multiple districts. She is pragmatic, cautious, and known for protecting her regular clients.Shade-11\line A skilled robot technician who runs a modification den. He offers gray-market augmentations and repairs, often helping people who can\u8217\'92t get help through official channels. He is professional, somewhat aloof, and has a strict personal code about who he will and won\u8217\'92t work with.Kai\line A young, ambitious human who works the Gossip Halls and information networks. He gathers and trades rumors, leads, and secrets. He walks the line between helpful informant and opportunistic hustler.Lira Solen (occasionally operates here)\line A human diplomat and information specialist who sometimes uses the Veil Market\u8217\'92s networks for sensitive negotiations or to acquire items the official system won\u8217\'92t provide.\u8220\'93The Broker\u8221\'94 (real name unknown)\line A mysterious, highly respected figure who runs one of the largest Shadow Auction Houses. Almost no one has met them in person \u8212\'97 deals are handled through trusted intermediaries. Their reputation for fairness (within the rules of the market) is legendary.}
\par \pard\plain \s21\rtlch\afs12 \ltrch\loch\sb0\sa283\brdrt\brdrnone\brdrl\brdrnone\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw1\brdrcf15\brsp0\brdrr\brdrnone\noline\fs12\ltrpar\loch

\par \pard\plain \s17\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Daily Life ExamplesExample 1: A Veteran Fixer\line Mira \u8220\'93Veil\u8221\'94 Kade starts her day checking new arrivals from the Undergrid in a hidden loading dock. She spends the afternoon meeting clients in a Fixer Bar, arranging everything from emergency medicine to restricted Arcanet codes. In the evening she hosts a small gathering in her safe lounge, trading favors and gathering information while keeping a close eye on who enters and leaves.Example 2: A Black-Market Technician\line Shade-11 works in his modification den performing careful augmentations and repairs for clients who need them for survival or work. He spends his evenings in one of the Shadow Auction Houses looking for new parts and keeping his ear to the ground for emerging threats or opportunities in the district.Example 3: A Bonded Smuggling Pair\line A human smuggler and her robot partner move goods through the Undergrid at night. During \u8220\'93daytime\u8221\'94 hours (often evening) they sell or trade what they acquired. They use their earnings to support family members in the Hearthward and maintain a hidden safehouse for when things get too hot.Example 4: A Desperate Resident\line Someone from the Havenward comes to the market looking for emergency heating parts or medicine during a blackout. They spend hours carefully negotiating prices, verifying quality, and building just enough trust with a merchant to make the deal \u8212\'97 knowing one mistake could be costly.}
