\par \pard\plain \s17\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
let's go into more detail with the Sagittarius district; specific types of locations, notable NPCs, daily life examples, etc)}
\par \pard\plain \s17\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Sagittarius District \u8211\'96 Frostward Reaches\line Expanded DetailSpecific Types of Locations1. The Outer Ring Domes\line Heavily reinforced multi-level domes designed to withstand extreme blizzards, ice quakes, and pressure. These are the main residential and operational hubs. They have thick insulated walls, redundant heating systems, and emergency blast doors.2. Kharkovchanka Depots & Vehicle Bays\line Large, rugged garages and maintenance facilities for the district\u8217\'92s fleet of heavy, cold-adapted transport vehicles. These bays are loud, oily, and constantly active with repairs and loading operations.3. Ice Harvesting & Resource Outposts\line Remote or semi-remote facilities where crews extract rare minerals, water ice, and exotic compounds from the glaciers. Some are fixed stations; others are mobile outposts that move with the ice.4. Frontier Watchtowers\line Elevated, heavily armored observation posts used for monitoring weather patterns, ice movements, and potential external threats. Many have long-range communication arrays.5. The Trailhead Commons\line The social and logistical heart of the district. A large central hub where expeditions are planned, supplies are traded, returning crews gather, and stories are shared. It functions as a combination of town square, bar, and planning room.6. Storm Shelters & Deep Bunkers\line Heavily fortified underground facilities stocked for surviving extreme, multi-day Antarctic storms. These are regularly drilled and maintained.7. The Edge Markets\line Informal trading posts where frontier goods \u8212\'97 rare materials, salvaged pre-war tech, preserved foods, furs, and custom tools \u8212\'97 are bought, sold, or bartered. These markets have a raw, practical atmosphere.8. Memorial Cairns\line Outdoor and semi-outdoor stone and metal monuments honoring explorers, harvesters, and workers lost to the ice. These are treated with quiet respect and are often visited before dangerous expeditions.}
\par \pard\plain \s21\rtlch\afs12 \ltrch\loch\sb0\sa283\brdrt\brdrnone\brdrl\brdrnone\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw1\brdrcf15\brsp0\brdrr\brdrnone\noline\fs12\ltrpar\loch

\par \pard\plain \s17\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Notable NPCs (Examples)Ranger Tor-22\line A veteran robot ice harvester and scout. Calm, highly competent, and respected for his ability to read ice conditions. He has survived multiple extreme storms and is often sought out for advice before major runs.Captain Lena Voss\line A tough, pragmatic human mechanic who runs one of the main vehicle bays. She is blunt, protective of her crew, and known for getting damaged Kharkovchankas back on the ice faster than anyone else.Elias \u8220\'93Icewalker\u8221\'94 Kane\line A human explorer and expedition leader with decades of experience. Charismatic and optimistic, he leads many of the longer resource runs and has a reputation for bringing his teams back alive even in bad conditions.Veyra-6\line A robot technician and vehicle specialist who works closely with human crews. She has a dry sense of humor and is known for making creative field repairs with limited parts.The \u8220\'93Old Guard\u8221\'94\line A loose group of Long Night War veterans (both human and robot) who never fully reintegrated into inner districts. They tend to keep to themselves but are deeply respected for their survival knowledge.}
\par \pard\plain \s21\rtlch\afs12 \ltrch\loch\sb0\sa283\brdrt\brdrnone\brdrl\brdrnone\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw1\brdrcf15\brsp0\brdrr\brdrnone\noline\fs12\ltrpar\loch

\par \pard\plain \s17\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Daily Life ExamplesExample 1: A Veteran Ice Harvester\line Tor-22 returns from a multi-day ice run with a load of rare minerals. He spends the morning securing his vehicle and offloading cargo at the depot. In the afternoon he performs maintenance and reports conditions at the Trailhead Commons. In the evening he shares stories and warnings with other returning crews over a hot meal, then rests before the next run.Example 2: A Human Frontier Mechanic\line Captain Lena Voss starts her day in the vehicle bays repairing storm-damaged Kharkovchankas. She spends the afternoon training apprentices and arguing with supply officers about scarce parts. In the evening she joins friends at the Trailhead Commons, swapping stories and keeping morale high during a brewing storm.Example 3: A Bonded Pioneer Pair\line A human scout and her robot partner prepare for a long ice expedition. They spend the day checking supplies, calibrating instruments, and saying quiet goodbyes to friends. They operate with a quiet understanding that every trip carries real risk, but they thrive on the independence and purpose the frontier gives them.Example 4: A Young New Arrival\line A newly arrived robot helps with habitat maintenance while learning frontier skills from veterans. He spends his evenings in the Trailhead Commons listening to stories, slowly adapting to the harsher, more independent lifestyle and the constant awareness of the ice outside.}
\par \pard\plain \s21\rtlch\afs12 \ltrch\loch\sb0\sa283\brdrt\brdrnone\brdrl\brdrnone\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw1\brdrcf15\brsp0\brdrr\brdrnone\noline\fs12\ltrpar\loch

