Virgo District \u8211\'96 Concordia UndergridOverview / Atmosphere\line The Undergrid is Concordia\u8217\'92s hidden foundation \u8212\'97 the vast, labyrinthine network of tunnels, maintenance shafts, utility corridors, and service levels beneath the city. It is dark, humid, echoing, and relentlessly practical. The air is thick with the smell of ozone, recycled lubricants, old metal, and damp concrete. Lighting is functional and harsh \u8212\'97 stark white work lamps, flickering emergency reds, and the occasional glow of diagnostic panels. This district feels ancient and alive at the same time. It is the place where perfectionists and pragmatists clash daily, where the city\u8217\'92s scars and secrets are laid bare. The Undergrid is not glamorous; it is essential. Residents here see themselves as the unsung backbone keeping everything above ground from collapsing.Physical Environment & Landmarks}
