Concordia Central Hub (13th District \u8211\'96 Neutral)Overview / Atmosphere\line The Central Hub is the literal and symbolic axis of Concordia \u8212\'97 the neutral heart where all districts converge. It is the political, logistical, and ceremonial core of the city. Unlike the specialized flavor of the other districts, the Hub feels like a pressure-cooker of overlapping priorities: formal yet chaotic, idealistic yet exhausted, grand yet increasingly makeshift.The atmosphere is one of controlled tension. Architecture is monumental and symmetrical \u8212\'97 grand halls, wide boulevards, and towering administrative spires \u8212\'97 but many areas now show signs of strain: temporary partitions, emergency generators, and patched-up infrastructure. Lighting is a mix of official neutral white and emergency amber. The air carries the scent of recycled oxygen, strong synthetic coffee, ink, and stressed bodies working long hours.This is the district where the city\u8217\'92s ideals of unity are constantly tested against the brutal reality of scarcity.Physical Environment & Landmarks}
